&lt;p&gt;Swansea Bay University Health Board is looking to recruit an enthusiastic and driven individual to the post of Senior Applications and Data Warehouse Developer. The primary responsibility of the post holder will be to lead on the specification, design and development of automated production processes for the health boards’ business intelligence (BI) solutions. This will involve using various BI platforms as well as SQL Server Management Studio and Integration Services.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This post will also support the direction of the infrastructure required in designing, developing and implementing a Digital Services Delivery Solution. The post holder will help to provide users with seamless access to information that will support service improvement and management, as well as continually seek innovative ways of using technology to support working practices and streamline processes within the Department, Directorate and the Health Board.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Joanne EmmsData Intelligence Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;joanne.emms@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
